3835#define M_NO_DEF_SUBTYPE M_NO_DEFAULT_TYPE(SUBTYPE)
3836#define M_NO_DEF_SUBTYPE_PTR M_NO_DEFAULT_TYPE(SUBTYPE_PTR)
3837#define M_NO_DEF_GENTYPE M_NO_DEFAULT_TYPE(GENTYPE)
3838#define M_NO_DEF_KEY_TYPE M_NO_DEFAULT_TYPE(KEY_TYPE)
3839#define M_NO_DEF_VALUE_TYPE M_NO_DEFAULT_TYPE(VALUE_TYPE)
3840#define M_NO_DEF_NAME M_NO_DEFAULT_TYPE(NAME) m_no_name
3841
3842/* Test if the given variable is a basic C variable:
3843 int, float, enum, bool or compatible.
3844 NOTE: Not perfect, but catch some errors */
3845#if defined(__STDC_VERSION__) && __STDC_VERSION__ >= 201112L
3846#define M_CHECK_BASIC_TYPE(a) \
3847 M_STATIC_ASSERT(_Generic(a, \
3848 _Bool: 1, \
3849 char: 1, unsigned char: 1, signed char: 1, \
3850 unsigned short: 1, signed short: 1, \
3851 unsigned int: 1, signed int: 1, \
3852 unsigned long: 1, signed long: 1, \
3853 unsigned long long: 1, signed long long:1, \
3854 float: 1, double:1, long double: 1, \
3855 char *:1, void*:1, \
3856 default: 0), \
3857 M_LIB_NOT_A_BASIC_TYPE, \
3858 "The variable " M_AS_STR(a) " is not a basic C type (int/float), " \
3859 "but the given methods use it like this. " \
3860 "It is likely the given oplist is not right.")
3861#else
3862#define M_CHECK_BASIC_TYPE(a) \
3863 M_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof (a) <= M_MAX(sizeof(long long), \
3864 M_MAX(sizeof (long double), \
3865 sizeof (uintmax_t))), \
3866 M_LIB_NOT_A_BASIC_TYPE, \
3867 "The variable " M_AS_STR(a) " is too big to be a basic C type (int/float), " \
3868 "but the given methods use it like this. " \
3869 "It is likely the given oplist is not right.")
3870#endif
3871
3872/* Check if both variables are of the same type.
3873 The test compare their size.
3874 NOTE: Not perfect but catch some errors */
3875#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__cplusplus)
3876#define M_CHECK_SAME(a, b) \
3877 M_STATIC_ASSERT(__builtin_types_compatible_p(__typeof__(a), __typeof__(b)), \
3878 M_LIB_NOT_SAME_TYPE, \
3879 "The variable " M_AS_STR(a) " and " M_AS_STR(b) \
3880 " are not of same type.")
3881#else
3882#define M_CHECK_SAME(a, b) \
3883 M_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(a) == sizeof(b), \
3884 M_LIB_NOT_SAME_TYPE, \
3885 "The variable " M_AS_STR(a) " and " M_AS_STR(b) \
3886 " are not of same type.")
3887#endif
3888
3889/* Check if the oplist is compatible with the type.
3890 The oplist should define a TYPE method, in which case it is tested.
3891 If it is not exported, do nothing.
3892 Compare the type in C11, the size in C99 or C++.
3893 - name is the base name of the container.
3894 - inst is a number which is incremented for each use of this macro
3895 within the named container.
3896 - type is the type to test
3897 - oplist of the oplist to test to.
3898*/
3899#if defined(__STDC_VERSION__) && __STDC_VERSION__ >= 201112L
3900#define M_CHECK_COMPATIBLE_OPLIST(name, inst, type, oplist) \
3901 M_IF_METHOD(TYPE, oplist) \
3902 ( \
3903 M_INLINE void M_C3(m_c0re_ctype_, name, inst)(void) \
3904 { \
3905 type x; \
3906 /* Proper check using _Generic */ \
3907 M_STATIC_ASSERT(_Generic(&x, \
3908 M_GET_TYPE oplist *: 1 /* Ok, type matches */, \
3909 default: 0 /* NOK, type doesn't match */ ), \
3910 M_LIB_TYPE_MISTMACH, \
3911 "The given type " M_AS_STR(type) \
3912 " and the type of the oplist does not match: " \
3913 M_OPL_AS_STR(oplist) ); \
3914 } \
3915 , /* End of TYPE */)
3916#else
3917#define M_CHECK_COMPATIBLE_OPLIST(name, inst, type, oplist) \
3918 M_IF_METHOD(TYPE, oplist) \
3919 ( \
3920 M_INLINE void M_C3(m_c0re_ctype_, name, inst)(void) \
3921 { \
3922 /* Imperfect check using size of type */ \
3923 M_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof (type) == sizeof (M_GET_TYPE oplist), \
3924 M_LIB_TYPE_MISTMACH, \
3925 "The given type " M_AS_STR(type) \
3926 " and the type of the oplist does not match: " \
3927 M_OPL_AS_STR(oplist) ); \
3928 } \
3929 , /* End of TYPE */)
3930#endif
3931
3932
3933/* Define the default method.
3934 NOTE: M_SET_DEFAULT may be called in conditions where a and b
3935 are different but compatible type.
3936 */
3937#define M_INIT_DEFAULT(a) ((a) = 0)
3938#define M_SET_DEFAULT(a,b) ((a) = (b))
3939#define M_NOTHING_DEFAULT(...) ((void)(__VA_ARGS__))
3940#define M_EMPTY_DEFAULT(...) ((void)1)
3941#define M_TRUE_DEFAULT(...) true
3942#define M_FALSE_DEFAULT(...) false
3943#define M_NEW_DEFAULT(a) M_MEMORY_ALLOC(a)
3944#define M_DEL_DEFAULT(a) M_MEMORY_DEL(a)
3945#define M_REALLOC_DEFAULT(t,p,s) M_MEMORY_REALLOC(t,p,s)
3946#define M_FREE_DEFAULT(a) M_MEMORY_FREE(a)
3947#define M_EQUAL_DEFAULT(a,b) ((a) == (b))
3948#define M_CMP_DEFAULT(a,b) ((a) < (b) ? -1 : (a) > (b))
3949#define M_ADD_DEFAULT(a,b,c) ((a) = (b) + (c))
3950#define M_SUB_DEFAULT(a,b,c) ((a) = (b) - (c))
3951#define M_MUL_DEFAULT(a,b,c) ((a) = (b) * (c))
3952#define M_DIV_DEFAULT(a,b,c) ((a) = (b) / (c))
3953#define M_AND_DEFAULT(a,b,c) ((a) = (b) & (c))
3954#define M_OR_DEFAULT(a,b,c) ((a) = (b) | (c))
3955#define M_NO_EXT_ALGO(n,co,to)
3956#define M_INC_ALLOC_DEFAULT(n) (M_MAX(8, (n))*2)
3957
3958/* Define the method for basic types */
3959/* Check that the type matches a C basic type and do the job */
3960#define M_INIT_BASIC(a) (M_CHECK_BASIC_TYPE(a), (a) = 0)
3961#define M_SET_BASIC(a,b) (M_CHECK_BASIC_TYPE(a), (a) = (b))
3962#define M_EQUAL_BASIC(a,b) (M_CHECK_BASIC_TYPE(a), (a) == (b))
3963#define M_CMP_BASIC(a,b) (M_CHECK_BASIC_TYPE(a), (a) < (b) ? -1 : (a) > (b))
3964
3965/* NOTE: Theses operators are NOT compatible with the '[1]' tricks
3966 if the variable is defined as a parameter of a function
3967 (sizeof (a) is not portable). */
3968#define M_MOVE_DEFAULT(a,b) (M_CHECK_SAME(a, b), M_MEMCPY_DEFAULT(a, b), memset(&(b), 0, sizeof (a)))
3969#define M_MEMCPY_DEFAULT(a,b) (M_CHECK_SAME(a, b), memcpy(&(a), &(b), sizeof (a)))
3970#define M_MEMSET_DEFAULT(a) (memset(&(a), 0, sizeof (a)))
3971#define M_MEMCMP1_DEFAULT(a,b) (M_CHECK_SAME(a, b), memcmp(&(a), &(b), sizeof (a)) == 0)
3972#define M_MEMCMP2_DEFAULT(a,b) (M_CHECK_SAME(a, b), memcmp(&(a), &(b), sizeof (a)))
3973#define M_SWAP_DEFAULT(el1, el2) do { \
3974 char _tmp[sizeof (el1)]; \
3975 M_CHECK_SAME(el1, el2); \
3976 memcpy(&_tmp, &(el1), sizeof (el1)); \
3977 memcpy(&(el1), &(el2), sizeof (el1)); \
3978 memcpy(&(el2), &_tmp, sizeof (el1)); \
3979 } while (0)
3980
3981/* NOTE: Theses operators are to be used with the '[1]' tricks
3982 if the variable is defined as a parameter of a function
3983 (sizeof (a) is not portable). */
3984#define M_MOVE_A1_DEFAULT(a,b) (M_CHECK_SAME(a[0], b[0]), M_MEMCPY_A1_DEFAULT(a, b), M_MEMSET_A1_DEFAULT(b))
3985#define M_MEMCPY_A1_DEFAULT(a,b) (M_CHECK_SAME(a[0], b[0]), memcpy(&(a[0]), &(b[0]), sizeof (a[0])))
3986#define M_MEMSET_A1_DEFAULT(a) (memset(&(a[0]), 0, sizeof (a[0])))
3987#define M_MEMCMP1_A1_DEFAULT(a,b) (M_CHECK_SAME(a[0],b[0]), memcmp(&(a[0]), &(b[0]), sizeof (a[0])) == 0)
3988#define M_MEMCMP2_A1_DEFAULT(a,b) (M_CHECK_SAME(a[0], b[0]), memcmp(&(a[0]), &(b[0]), sizeof (a[0])))
3989#define M_HASH_A1_DEFAULT(a) (m_core_hash((const void*) &(a[0]), sizeof (a[0])) )

4112/* Define helper functions for enum oplist */
4113/* Input/Output an enumerate.
4114 It is stored as a long long integer for best compatibility. */
4115#if M_USE_STDIO
4116M_INLINE long long
4117m_core_fscan_enum (FILE *f)
4118{
4119 long long ret;
4120 int s = m_core_fscanf(f, "%lld", &ret) == 1;
4121 /* HACK: Push back the return code in FILE stream,
4122 so that it can be popped later with a fgetc */
4123 ungetc(s, f);
4124 return ret;
4125}
4126#define M_ENUM_FPRINT(f, var) fprintf( (f), "%lld", (long long) (var))
4127#define M_ENUM_FSCAN(oplist, var, f) \
4128 ( var = (M_GET_TYPE oplist) (true ? m_core_fscan_enum(f) : 0), fgetc(f))
4129#endif /* M_USE_STDIO */
4130
4131/* HACK: Parse two times to convert and then compute
4132 if the conversion succeeds for PARSE */
4133M_INLINE long long
4134m_core_parse1_enum (const char str[])
4135{
4136 return strtoll(str, NULL, 10);
4137}
4138M_INLINE bool
4139m_core_parse2_enum (const char str[], const char **endptr)
4140{
4141 char *end;
4142 strtoll(str, &end, 10);
4143 if (endptr != NULL) *endptr = end;
4144 return end != str;
4145}

4147#define M_ENUM_OUT_SERIAL(serial, var) \
4148 ((serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, (long long) (var), sizeof (var)))
4149#define M_ENUM_IN_SERIAL(oplist, var, serial) \
4150 ( var = (M_GET_TYPE oplist)(true ? m_core_in_serial_enum(serial) : 0), (serial)->tmp.r)
4151#define M_ENUM_GET_STR(str, var, append) \
4152 ((append ? m_string_cat_printf : m_string_printf) (str, "%lld", (long long) (var) ))
4153#define M_ENUM_PARSE(oplist, var, str, endptr) \
4154 ( var = (M_GET_TYPE oplist) (true ? m_core_parse1_enum(str) : 0), m_core_parse2_enum(str, endptr))

4187/* From an oplist (...) return ... (Like M_ID but for OPLIST) */
4188#define M_OPFLAT(...) __VA_ARGS__
4189
4190/* Concat two oplists in one. op1 will have higher priority to op2 */
4191#define M_OPCAT(op1,op2) (M_OPFLAT op1, M_OPFLAT op2)
4192
4193/* Apply an oplist */
4194#define M_OPAPPLY(a, oplist) a oplist
4195
4196/* Extend an oplist by adding some methods */
4197#define M_OPEXTEND(op, ...) (__VA_ARGS__, M_OPFLAT op)
4198
4199/* Return the content of a property named 'propname'
4200 in the PROPERTIES field of oplist
4201 or 0, if it is not defined */
4202#define M_GET_PROPERTY(oplist, propname) \
4203 M_GET_METHOD (propname, 0, M_OPFLAT M_GET_PROPERTIES oplist)
4204
4205/* Test if a method is present in an oplist.
4206 Return 0 (method is absent or disabled) or 1 (method is present and not disabled).
4207 NOTE: M_TEST_METHOD_P does not work if method is something within parenthesis (like OPLIST*)
4208 In this case, you shall use the M_TEST_METHOD_ALTER_P macro (safer but slower).
4209 */
4210#define M_TEST_METHOD_P(method, oplist) \
4211 M_BOOL(M_GET_METHOD (method, 0, M_OPFLAT oplist))
4212
4213#define M_TEST_METHOD_ALTER_P(method, oplist) \
4214 M_INV(M_EMPTY_P(M_GET_METHOD (method, , M_OPFLAT oplist)))
4215
4216
4217/* Test if a method is disabled in an oplist.
4218 To disable an oplist, just put '0' in the method like this:
4219 Example: (INIT(0), CLEAR(clear))
4220 Here INIT is disabled, whereas CLEAR is not.
4221 Return 1 (method is disabled) or 0 (method is not disabled - absent or present) */
4222#define M_TEST_DISABLED_METHOD_P(method, oplist) \
4223 M_INV(M_BOOL(M_GET_METHOD (method, 1, M_OPFLAT oplist)))
4224
4225/* Perfom a preprocessing M_IF, if the method is present in the oplist.
4226 Example: M_IF_METHOD(HASH, oplist)(define function with HASH method, ) */
4227#define M_IF_METHOD(method, oplist) M_IF(M_TEST_METHOD_P(method, oplist))
4228
4229/* Perfom a preprocessing M_IF, if the method is disabled in the oplist.
4230 Example: M_IF_DISABLED_METHOD(HASH, oplist)(define function without HASH method, ) */
4231#define M_IF_DISABLED_METHOD(method, oplist) M_IF(M_TEST_DISABLED_METHOD_P(method, oplist))
4232
4233/* Perform a preprocessing M_IF if the method exists in both oplist.
4234 Example: M_IF_METHOD_BOTH(HASH, oplist1, oplist2) (define function with HASH method, ) */
4235#define M_IF_METHOD_BOTH(method, oplist1, oplist2) \
4236 M_IF(M_AND(M_TEST_METHOD_P(method, oplist1), M_TEST_METHOD_P(method, oplist2)))
4237
4238/* Perform a preprocessing M_IF if both methods exist in the oplist.
4239 Example: M_IF_METHOD2(HASH, CMP, oplist) (define function with HASH & CMP method, ) */
4240#define M_IF_METHOD2(method1, method2, oplist) \
4241 M_IF(M_AND(M_TEST_METHOD_P(method1, oplist), M_TEST_METHOD_P(method2, oplist)))
4242
4243/* Perform a preprocessing M_IF if at least one method exists in the oplist.
4244 Example: M_IF_AT_LEAST_METHOD(HASH, CMP, oplist) (define function with HASH or CMP method, ) */
4245#define M_IF_AT_LEAST_METHOD(method1, method2, oplist) \
4246 M_IF(M_OR(M_TEST_METHOD_P(method1, oplist), M_TEST_METHOD_P(method2, oplist)))
4247
4248/* Perform a preprocessing M_IF if both methods exists in both oplist.
4249 Example: M_IF_METHOD2_BOTH(HASH, INIT, oplist1, oplist2) (define function with HASH & INIT method, ) */
4250#define M_IF_METHOD2_BOTH(method1, method2, oplist1, oplist2) \
4251 M_IF(M_AND(M_AND(M_TEST_METHOD_P(method1, oplist1), M_TEST_METHOD_P(method1, oplist2)), \
4252 M_AND(M_TEST_METHOD_P(method2, oplist1), M_TEST_METHOD_P(method2, oplist2))))
4253
4254/* Perform a preprocessing M_IF if the method exists for all oplist.
4255 Example: M_IF_METHOD_ALL(HASH, oplist1, oplist2) (define function with HASH method, ) */
4256#define M_IF_METHOD_ALL(method, ...) \
4257 M_IF(M_REDUCE2(M_TEST_METHOD_P, M_AND, method, __VA_ARGS__))
4258
4259/* Perform a preprocessing M_IF if both methods exist for all oplist.
4260 Example: M_IF_METHOD2_ALL(HASH, INIT, oplist1, oplist2) (define function with HASH & INIT methods, ) */
4261#define M_IF_METHOD2_ALL(method1, method2, ...) \
4262 M_IF(M_REDUCE2(M_TEST_METHOD2_P, M_AND, (method1, method2), __VA_ARGS__))
4263#define M_TEST_METHOD2_P(method_pair, oplist) \
4264 M_AND(M_TEST_METHOD_P(M_PAIR_1 method_pair, oplist), M_TEST_METHOD_P(M_PAIR_2 method_pair, oplist))
4265
4266/* By putting this after a method in an oplist, we transform the argument list
4267 so that the first argument becomes a pointer to the destination (OBSOLETE MACRO) */
4268#define M_IPTR(...) ( & __VA_ARGS__ )
4269
4270/* Perform an INIT_MOVE if present, or emulate it using INIT_SET/CLEAR */
4271#define M_DO_INIT_MOVE(oplist, dest, src) do { \
4272 M_IF_METHOD(INIT_MOVE, oplist)(M_CALL_INIT_MOVE(oplist, (dest), (src)), \
4273 M_CALL_INIT_SET(oplist, (dest), (src)) ; \
4274 M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, (src) )); \
4275 } while (0)
4276
4277/* Perform a MOVE if present, or emulate it using CLEAR/INIT_MOVE
4278 if possible, or with SET/CLEAR otherwise */
4279#define M_DO_MOVE(oplist, dest, src) do { \
4280 M_IF_METHOD(MOVE, oplist) (M_CALL_MOVE(oplist, (dest), (src)), \
4281 M_IF_METHOD(INIT_MOVE, oplist)(M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, (dest)); \
4282 M_CALL_INIT_MOVE(oplist, (dest), (src)), \
4283 M_CALL_SET(oplist, (dest), (src)); \
4284 M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, (src)) \
4285 )); \
4286 } while (0)
4287
4288/* Provide SET semantics through INIT_SET. Needs API_1 */
4289#define M_SET_THROUGH_INIT_SET(oplist, dst, src) \
4290 ( M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, dst), M_CALL_INIT_SET(oplist, dst, src) )
4291
4292/* Test if the argument is an expression that looks like an oplist:
4293 * - the data are within parenthesis
4294 * - there is only one level of parenthesis
4295 * The detection is imperfect.
4296*/
4297#define M_OPLIST_P(a) \
4298 M_AND(M_PARENTHESIS_P(a), M_INV(M_PARENTHESIS_P (M_OPFLAT a)))
4299
4300#define M_IF_OPLIST(a) M_IF(M_OPLIST_P(a))
4301
4302/* If 'a' seems to be an oplist, it returns a,
4303 else if a symbol composed of M_OPL_##a() exists and is defined as an oplist, it returns it
4304 else it returns a (but it is likely to fail latter).
4305 In short, if a global oplist is defined for the argument, it returns it
4306 otherwise it returns the argument.
4307 Global oplist is limited to typedef types.
4308 We need to delay the concat between M_OPL_ and a until we know it cannot be an oplist
4309 as if a is an oplist the concat of M_OPL_ and an oplist will produce an illegal token.
4310*/
4311#define M_GLOBAL_OPLIST(a) \
4312 M_IF( M_OPLIST_P(a))(M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_ID, M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_ELSE)(a)
4313#define M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_ID(a) a
4314#define M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_ELSE(a) M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_ELSE2(a, M_C(M_OPL_, a)())
4315#define M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_ELSE2(a, op) M_IF( M_OPLIST_P (op))(op, a)
4316
4317#define M_GLOBAL_TYPE(a) \
4318 M_IF( M_OPLIST_P(a))(M_GLOBALI_TYPE_GET, M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_ID)(a)
4319#define M_GLOBALI_TYPE_GET(a) M_GET_TYPE a
4320
4321/* If a symbol composed of M_OPL_##a() exists and is defined as an oplist,
4322 it returns it otherwise it returns M_BASIC_OPLIST.
4323 Global oplist is limited to typedef types.
4324 NOTE1: It first tests if the type doesn't start with a parenthesis,
4325 in which case concatenation cannot be used.
4326 NOTE: It doesn't test if M_OPL_##a() is exactly an oplist (M_OPLIST_P)
4327 but rather than if it starts with parenthesis: this is to allow
4328 M_OPL_a() to expand into an invalid oplist ((M_LIB_ERROR()))
4329 NOTE: The result of this macro shall be evaluated like this:
4330 M_GLOBAL_OPLIST_OR_DEF(type)()
4331*/
4332#define M_GLOBAL_OPLIST_OR_DEF(a) \
4333 M_IF( M_PARENTHESIS_P(a))(M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_DEFAULT1, M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_OR_DEF_ELSE)(a)
4334#define M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_DEFAULT1(a) M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_DEFAULT2
4335#define M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_DEFAULT2() M_BASIC_OPLIST
4336#define M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_OR_DEF_ELSE(a) M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_OR_DEF_ELSE2(a, M_C(M_OPL_, a)())
4337#define M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_OR_DEF_ELSE2(a, op) M_IF( M_PARENTHESIS_P(op))(M_C(M_OPL_, a), M_GLOBALI_OPLIST_DEFAULT2)
4338
4339
4340/* Register simple classic C types (no qualifier)
4341 * We cannot register type with qualifier (for example long long) however.
4342 */
4343#define M_OPL_char() M_BASIC_OPLIST
4344#define M_OPL_short() M_BASIC_OPLIST
4345#define M_OPL_int() M_BASIC_OPLIST
4346#define M_OPL_unsigned() M_BASIC_OPLIST
4347#define M_OPL_long() M_BASIC_OPLIST
4348#define M_OPL_float() M_BASIC_OPLIST
4349#define M_OPL_double() M_BASIC_OPLIST
4350#define M_OPL_bool() M_BOOL_OPLIST
4351#define M_OPL__Bool() M_BOOL_OPLIST
4352

4354/************************************************************/
4355/******************** Syntax Enhancing **********************/
4356/************************************************************/
4357
4358/* M_EACH enables iterating over a container using a for loop.
4359 First argument will be a created pointer var to the underlying type.
4360 Second argument is the container to iterate.
4361 Third argument can be the oplist of the list or the type of the list if a global
4362 oplist has been recorded.
4363 USAGE: for M_EACH(item, list, LIST_OPLIST) { action; }
4364*/
4365#define M_EACH(item, container, oplist) \
4366 M_EACHI_OPLIST(item, container, M_GLOBAL_OPLIST(oplist))
4367
4368/* Internal for M_EACH */
4369#define M_EACHI_OPLIST(item, container, oplist) \
4370 M_IF_METHOD(IT_REF, oplist)(M_EACHI, M_EACHI_CONST) \
4371 (item, container, oplist, M_C(local_iterator_, __LINE__), \
4372 M_C(local_cont_, __LINE__))
4373
4374/* Internal for M_EACH with M_GET_IT_REF operator */
4375#define M_EACHI(item,container,oplist, iterator, cont) \
4376 (bool cont = true; cont; cont = false) \
4377 for(M_GET_SUBTYPE oplist *item; cont ; cont = false) \
4378 for(M_GET_IT_TYPE oplist iterator; cont ; cont = false) \
4379 for(M_GET_IT_FIRST oplist (iterator, container) ; \
4380 !M_GET_IT_END_P oplist (iterator) \
4381 && (item = M_GET_IT_REF oplist (iterator), true) ; \
4382 M_GET_IT_NEXT oplist (iterator))
4383
4384/* Internal for M_EACH with M_GET_IT_CREF operator */
4385#define M_EACHI_CONST(item,container,oplist, iterator, cont) \
4386 (bool cont = true; cont; cont = false) \
4387 for(const M_GET_SUBTYPE oplist *item; cont ; cont = false) \
4388 for(M_GET_IT_TYPE oplist iterator; cont ; cont = false) \
4389 for(M_GET_IT_FIRST oplist (iterator, container) ; \
4390 !M_GET_IT_END_P oplist (iterator) \
4391 && (item = M_GET_IT_CREF oplist (iterator), true) ; \
4392 M_GET_IT_NEXT oplist (iterator))
4393
4394
4395/* M_LET defines, initializes & clears an object available within the next bracket.
4396 USAGE:
4397 M_LET(variable_list, variable_oplist|variable_type) { code }
4398 * variable_list can be a comma separated list of variable.
4399 * A variable alone is initialized to its default value.
4400 * A variable with initializer (like '(var, init value...)'
4401 is initialized with this init values.
4402 NOTE: The code within {} can not perform return or goto command.
4403 break is supported and will exit the braket (calling the clear method)
4404 Last argument can be the oplist or the type itself if a global
4405 oplist has been recorded for this type.
4406 */
4407#define M_LET(a, ...) \
4408 M_ID(M_LETI0 ((M_REVERSE(a, __VA_ARGS__, \
4409 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P(a))(M_LETI_VAR_NAME_A, \
4410 M_LETI_VAR_NAME_B)(a) ))))
4411
4412// 1b. Generate a unique name based on the first variable and the line number
4413#define M_LETI_VAR_NAME_A(var) M_C3(_local_cont_, M_RET_ARG1 var, __LINE__)
4414#define M_LETI_VAR_NAME_B(var) M_C3(_local_cont_, var, __LINE__)
4415// 2. Evaluate with or without and inject oplist
4416#define M_LETI0(list) \
4417 M_LETI1 list
4418#define M_LETI1(cont, oplist, ...) \
4419 M_LETI2(cont, M_GLOBAL_OPLIST(oplist), __VA_ARGS__)
4420// 3. Validate oplist before going any further
4421#define M_LETI2(cont, oplist, ...) \
4422 M_IF_OPLIST(oplist)(M_LETI3, M_LETI2_FAILURE)(cont, oplist, __VA_ARGS__)
4423// Stop with a failure (invalid oplist)
4424#define M_LETI2_FAILURE(cont, oplist, ...) \
4425 M_STATIC_ASSERT(false, M_LIB_NOT_AN_OPLIST, "(M_LET): the given argument is not a valid oplist: " M_AS_STR(oplist))
4426// 4. Map all variables to their own LET
4427#define M_LETI3(cont, oplist, ...) \
4428 for(bool cont = true; cont ; /* unused */) \
4429 M_MAP2(M_LETI_SINGLE, (cont, oplist), __VA_ARGS__) \
4430 for(;cont;cont = false)
4431// 5. Dispatch the right LET in function of having or not arguments with data = (cont, oplist)
4432#define M_LETI_SINGLE(data, name) \
4433 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P(name))(M_LETI_SINGLE2_SET,M_LETI_SINGLE2) \
4434 (M_PAIR_1 data, M_PAIR_2 data, name, M_RET_ARG1 name, M_SKIPI_1 name)
4435// 6a. Define without argument ==> use the INIT operator
4436#define M_LETI_SINGLE2(cont, oplist, name, ...) \
4437 M_LET_TRY_INJECT_PRE(cont, oplist, name) \
4438 for(M_GET_TYPE oplist name; \
4439 cont && (M_CALL_INIT(oplist, name), true); \
4440 (M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, name), cont = false)) \
4441 M_LET_TRY_INJECT_POST(cont, oplist, name)
4442// 6b. Define with arguments ==> use the INIT_SET or INIT_WITH operator (if defined).
4443#define M_LETI_SINGLE2_SET(cont, oplist, params, name, ...) \
4444 M_LET_TRY_INJECT_PRE(cont, oplist, name) \
4445 for(M_GET_TYPE oplist name; \
4446 cont && (M_LETI_SINGLE2_INIT(oplist, name, __VA_ARGS__), true); \
4447 (M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, name), cont = false)) \
4448 M_LET_TRY_INJECT_POST(cont, oplist, name)
4449// 6c. Use of INIT_SET or INIT_WITH.
4450#define M_LETI_SINGLE2_INIT(oplist, name, ...) \
4451 M_IF_METHOD(INIT_WITH,oplist)(M_LETI_SINGLE3_INIT, M_CALL_INIT_SET)(oplist, name, __VA_ARGS__)
4452#define M_LETI_SINGLE3_INIT(oplist, name, ...) \
4453 M_IF(M_NOTEQUAL( M_NARGS(__VA_ARGS__), 1))(M_CALL_INIT_WITH, M_LETI_SINGLE4_INIT)(oplist, name, __VA_ARGS__)
4454#define M_LETI_SINGLE4_INIT(oplist, name, arg) \
4455 M_IF(M_GET_PROPERTY(oplist, LET_AS_INIT_WITH))(M_CALL_INIT_WITH, M_LETI_SINGLE5_INIT)(oplist, name, arg)
4456#define M_LETI_SINGLE5_INIT(oplist, name, arg) \
4457 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P( arg ) )(M_CALL_INIT_WITH, M_CALL_INIT_SET)(oplist, name, M_REMOVE_PARENTHESIS (arg))
4458
4459/* Dummy stubs that do nothing by default (overrided if needed by m-try) */
4460#define M_LET_TRY_INJECT_PRE(cont, oplist, name)
4461#define M_LET_TRY_INJECT_POST(cont, oplist, name)
4462
4463/*
4464 * Internal M_LET for use within container.
4465 * Declare the given variable of the given type and
4466 * initialize / clear it using the given oplist .
4467 *
4468 * index shall be a number within the function (from 1)
4469 * identifying the M_QLET in the service.
4470*/
4471#define M_QLET(index, var, type, oplist) \
4472 M_LET(var, M_OPEXTEND(oplist, TYPE(type)))
4473
4474/* Transform the va list by adding their number as the first argument of
4475 the list.
4476 Example: M_VA(a,b,c,d,e) ==> 5,a,b,c,d,e
4477 TODO: Use of a structure instead of an integer to ensure limited syntax control.
4478*/
4479#define M_VA(...) M_NARGS(__VA_ARGS__), __VA_ARGS__
4480
4481
4482/* Defer the evaluation of the given expression until the closing brace.
4483 M_DEFER(code) { }
4484 Example:
4485 M_DEFER(free(p)) {
4486 // code using p
4487 } // Here p is free
4488*/
4489#define M_DEFER(...) \
4490 M_DEFER_INTERNAL(M_C(m_var_, __LINE__), __VA_ARGS__)
4491
4492#define M_DEFER_INTERNAL(cont, ...) \
4493 for(bool cont = true; cont; cont = false) \
4494 M_DEFER_TRY_INJECT_PRE(cont, __VA_ARGS__) \
4495 for( (void) 0; cont ; (__VA_ARGS__), cont = false) \
4496 M_DEFER_TRY_INJECT_POST(cont, __VA_ARGS__) \
4497 for( (void) 0; cont; cont = false)
4498
4499// Theses macros will be overrided by m-try if needed.
4500#define M_DEFER_TRY_INJECT_PRE(cont, clear) /* Nothing */
4501#define M_DEFER_TRY_INJECT_POST(cont, clear) /* Nothing */
4502
4503
4504/* If exceptions are activated, M_CHAIN_INIT enables support for chaining
4505 initialization at the begining of a constructor for the fields of the constructed
4506 object so that even if the constructor failed and throw an exception,
4507 the fields of the constructed object are properly cleared.
4508 This is equivalent to C++ construct: void type() : field1(), field2() { rest of constructor }
4509 M_CHAIN_INIT shall be the first instruction of the init function.
4510 Second argument is the initialization code.
4511 Third argument is the clear code.
4512 The clear code is *only* executed on exception.
4513 USAGE:
4514 void init_function(struct_t s) {
4515 M_CHAIN_INIT(name, string_init(s->str), string_clear(s->str)) {
4516 // Rest of initialization code
4517 }
4518 }
4519 */
4520#define M_CHAIN_INIT(name, init, clear) \
4521 M_CHAIN_INIT_INTERNAL(M_C(m_var_, name), init, clear)
4522
4523#define M_CHAIN_INIT_INTERNAL(cont, init, clear) \
4524 for(bool cont = true; cont; cont = false) \
4525 M_DEFER_TRY_INJECT_PRE(cont, clear) \
4526 for( init; cont ; cont = false) \
4527 M_DEFER_TRY_INJECT_POST(cont, clear) \
4528 for( (void) 0; cont; cont = false)
4529
4530
4531/* If exceptions are activated, M_CHAIN_OBJ enables support for chaining
4532 initialization at the begining of a constructor for the fields of the constructed
4533 object so that even if the constructor failed and throw an exception,
4534 the fields of the constructed object are properly cleared.
4535 This is equivalent to M_CHAIN_INIT except it takes an oplist.
4536 This is equivalent to C++ construct: void type() : field1(), field2() { rest of constructor }
4537 M_CHAIN_OBJ shall be the first instruction of the init function except
4538 it can be freely mixed with M_CHAIN_INIT
4539 First argument is a name identifier.
4540 Second argument is the oplist of the variable to initialize.
4541 Third argument is the variable to initialize.
4542 Optional fourth argument is the value to use for initialization.
4543 If there is no value, it will initialize using the INIT method.
4544 Otherwise, if there is no parenthesis around the value, it will use the INIT_SET method.
4545 Otherwise the INIT_WITH method.
4546 The clear code is *only* executed on exception.
4547 If the property NOCLEAR is defined for the object,
4548 it won't generate an exception handler at all even if exceptions are activated,
4549 and will only initialize the object.
4550 USAGE:
4551 void init_function(struct_t s) {
4552 M_CHAIN_OBJ(name, STRING_OPLIST, s->str ) {
4553 // Rest of initialization code
4554 }
4555 }
4556 */
4557#define M_CHAIN_OBJ(name, oplist, ...) \
4558 M_BY_NARGS( M_IF(M_GET_PROPERTY(oplist, NOCLEAR))(M_CHAIN_OBJ_A, M_CHAIN_OBJ_B), __VA_ARGS__) \
4559 (name, oplist, __VA_ARGS__)
4560// Need to define an exception handler. Use of M_CHAIN_INIT
4561#define M_CHAIN_OBJ_B__1(name, oplist, var) \
4562 M_CHAIN_INIT( name, M_CALL_INIT(oplist, var), M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, var) )
4563#define M_CHAIN_OBJ_B__2(name, oplist, var, value) \
4564 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P(value))(M_CHAIN_OBJ_B__2_WITH, M_CHAIN_OBJ_B__2_SET) \
4565 (name, oplist, var, value)
4566#define M_CHAIN_OBJ_B__2_WITH(name, oplist, var, value) \
4567 M_CHAIN_INIT( name, M_CALL_INIT_WITH(oplist, var, value), M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, var) )
4568#define M_CHAIN_OBJ_B__2_SET(name, oplist, var, value) \
4569 M_CHAIN_INIT( name, M_CALL_INIT_SET(oplist, var, value), M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, var) )
4570// No need to define an exception handler. Just call the INIT function.
4571#define M_CHAIN_OBJ_A__1(name, oplist, var) \
4572 M_CHAIN_FOR(name, M_CALL_INIT(oplist, var) )
4573#define M_CHAIN_OBJ_A__2(name, oplist, var, value) \
4574 M_CHAIN_FOR(name, \
4575 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P(value))(M_CALL_INIT_WITH, M_CALL_INIT_SET) \
4576 (oplist, var, value) )
4577
4578// Execute the 'init' function in a for loop construct
4579#define M_CHAIN_FOR(name, init ) \
4580 M_CHAIN_FOR_B(M_C(m_var_, name), init)
4581#define M_CHAIN_FOR_B(cont, init) \
4582 for(bool cont = true; cont; cont = false) \
4583 for( init; cont ; cont = false) \
4584 for( (void) 0; cont; cont = false)
4585
4586
4587/* If exceptions are activated, M_ON_EXCEPTION enables support for fixing
4588 the data structure when an exception is throw,
4589 so that the data structure integrity is ready for the CLEAR method.
4590 The fix code is *only* executed on exception.
4591 USAGE:
4592 void init_function(struct_t s) {
4593 M_ON_EXCEPTION(s->size = i ) {
4594 // Rest of initialization code
4595 }
4596 }
4597 Do nothing if exceptions are not enabled.
4598 */
4599#define M_ON_EXCEPTION(...) for(bool cont = true; cont; cont = false) \
4600
4601/* If exceptions are activated, M_IF_EXCEPTION will expand the code.
4602 Do nothing if exceptions are not enabled. */
4603#define M_IF_EXCEPTION(...) (void) 0
4604
4605/* Declare a variable as volatile if exceptions are enabled */
4606#define m_volatile /* nothing */
4607
4608
4609/* Declare a variable, initialize it, continue if the initialization succeeds,
4610 and clears the variable afterwards.
4611 Otherwise, stop the execution and execute else_code if defined.
4612 M_LET_IF(init code, test code, clear code[, else_code]) { code using the variable }
4613 Example:
4614 M_LET_IF(void * p = malloc(100), p!=0, free(p)) {
4615 // code using p
4616 } // Here p is free
4617*/
4618#define M_LET_IF(init, test, ...) \
4619 M_IF_NARGS_EQ1(__VA_ARGS__) \
4620 ( \
4621 M_LET_IF_INTERNAL (init, test, __VA_ARGS__, (void)0, M_C(m_var_, __LINE__)), \
4622 M_LET_IF_INTERNAL (init, test, __VA_ARGS__, M_C(m_var_, __LINE__)) \
4623 )
4624
4625#define M_LET_IF_INTERNAL(init, test, clear, else_a, cont) \
4626 for(bool cont = true; cont; cont = false) \
4627 for( init ; cont && ( (test) || (else_a, false) ); cont = false) \
4628 M_DEFER_INTERNAL(M_C(cont, defer), clear )
4629
4630
4631
4632/************************************************************/
4633/******************* INIT_WITH Enhancing ********************/
4634/************************************************************/
4635
4636/* Add as suffix for the given function the number of arguments of the calls
4637 equal to __ # NARGS(...)
4638 Can be used to call different function in function of the number of arguments.
4639 It doesn't call the function with the argument in order to be able to chain the
4640 macro */
4641#define M_BY_NARGS(function, ...) M_C3(function, __, M_NARGS(__VA_ARGS__))
4642
4643/* Call different methods in function of the number of arguments of the call,
4644 * to be used in an OPLIST for the INIT_WITH operator.
4645 * Shall be used with API_1 call (example INIT_WITH(API_1(M_INIT_WITH_NVAR)) )
4646 * Shall define a NAME base method
4647 * All INIT_WITH methods shall be named as name ## _init_with__ ## NARGS
4648 */
4649#define M_INIT_WITH_NVAR(oplist, ...) \
4650 M_BY_NARGS(M_C(M_GET_NAME oplist, _init_with), __VA_ARGS__)(__VA_ARGS__)
4651
4652
4653/* Initialize the container 'dest' as per 'oplist' INIT operator
4654 and fill it with the given VA_ARGS arguments with the PUSH operator.
4655 NOTE: If the REVERSE operator exists, it assumes a list,
4656 so it reverses the final order.
4657*/
4658#define M_INIT_VAI(oplist, dest, ...) \
4659 (void)(M_GET_INIT oplist (dest) , \
4660 M_MAP2_C(M_INIT_VAI_FUNC, (dest, M_GET_PUSH oplist) , __VA_ARGS__) \
4661 M_IF_METHOD(REVERSE, oplist)(M_DEFERRED_COMMA M_GET_REVERSE oplist (dest), ) \
4662 )
4663#define M_INIT_VAI_FUNC(d, a) \
4664 M_PAIR_2 d (M_PAIR_1 d, a)
4665
4666
4667/* Initialize the container 'dest' as per 'oplist' INIT operator
4668 and fill it with the given VA_ARGS arguments with the _push_raw method
4669 allowing INIT_WITH operator for the pushed argument if the given
4670 argument is between parenthesis, otherwise an INIT_SET is performed.
4671 NOTE: Parenthesis detection is the best we can do to detect a special
4672 argument. The argument may start with '*' or a '+' and we cannot use
4673 M_KEYWORD_P with such arguments (as it cannot be concatened).
4674 NOTE: If the REVERSE operator exists, it assumes a list,
4675 so it reverses the final order.
4676*/
4677#define M_INIT_WITH_VAI(oplist, dest, ...) \
4678 (void)(M_GET_INIT oplist (dest) , \
4679 M_MAP2_C(M_INIT_WITH_VAI22_FUNC, (dest, oplist) , __VA_ARGS__) \
4680 M_IF_METHOD(REVERSE, oplist)(M_DEFERRED_COMMA M_GET_REVERSE oplist(dest), ) \
4681 )
4682#define M_INIT_WITH_VAI22_FUNC(pair, a) \
4683 M_INIT_WITH_VAI23_FUNC(M_PAIR_1 pair, M_PAIR_2 pair, a)
4684
4685/* We first push a raw new item, and then we get back its pointer using _back.
4686 _back (contrary to _push_raw) has no side effect, and so is safe to be used
4687 in a macro */
4688#define M_INIT_WITH_VAI23_FUNC(d, op, a) \
4689 ( \
4690 (void) M_C(M_GET_NAME op, _push_raw)(d), \
4691 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P(a)) \
4692 (M_CALL_INIT_WITH, M_CALL_INIT_SET) \
4693 (M_GET_OPLIST op, *M_C(M_GET_NAME op, _back)(d), M_REMOVE_PARENTHESIS(a)) \
4694 )
4695
4696
4697/* Initialize the container 'dest' as per 'oplist' INIT operator
4698 and fill it with the given VA_ARGS arguments with the _emplace method
4699 if the given argument is between parenthesis, otherwise an _init_set
4700 is performed.
4701 NOTE: Parenthesis detection is the best we can do to detect a special
4702 argument. The argument may start with '*' or a '+' and we cannot use
4703 M_KEYWORD_P with such arguments (as it cannot be concatened).
4704 NOTE: If the REVERSE operator exists, it assumes a list,
4705 so it reverses the final order.
4706*/
4707#define M_INIT_EMPLACE_VAI(oplist, dest, ...) \
4708 (void)(M_GET_INIT oplist (dest) , \
4709 M_MAP2_C(M_INIT_EMPLACE_VAI2_FUNC, (dest, oplist) , __VA_ARGS__) \
4710 M_IF_METHOD(REVERSE, oplist)(M_DEFERRED_COMMA M_GET_REVERSE oplist(dest), ) \
4711 )
4712#define M_INIT_EMPLACE_VAI2_FUNC(pair, a) \
4713 M_INIT_EMPLACE_VAI3_FUNC(M_PAIR_1 pair, M_PAIR_2 pair, a)
4714#define M_INIT_EMPLACE_VAI3_FUNC(d, op, a) \
4715 ( \
4716 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P(a)) \
4717 (M_C(M_GET_NAME op, _emplace)(d, M_REMOVE_PARENTHESIS_3 a), \
4718 M_CALL_PUSH(op, d, a)) \
4719 )
4720
4721
4722/* Initialize the container 'dest' as per 'oplist' INIT operator
4723 and fill it with the given VA argument
4724 assumed to be pair (key,value) with the SET_KEY operator.
4725 If key (resp. value) is itself in the form ( ) and the
4726 oplist defined an EMPLACE_TYPE operator, performs an emplace insertion
4727 by construction an emplace call with no suffix.
4728*/
4729#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI(oplist, dest, ...) \
4730 (void)(M_GET_INIT oplist (dest) , \
4731 M_MAP2_C(M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P1, (dest, oplist) , __VA_ARGS__))
4732#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P1(dst_op, a) \
4733 M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2(M_PAIR_1 dst_op, M_PAIR_2 dst_op, M_PAIR_1 a, M_PAIR_2 a)
4734#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2(dst, oplist, key, value) \
4735 M_IF(M_AND(M_PARENTHESIS_P(key), M_TEST_METHOD_P(EMPLACE_TYPE, M_GET_KEY_OPLIST oplist))) \
4736 (M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2Y, M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2N)(dst, oplist, key, value)
4737#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2Y(dst, oplist, key, value) \
4738 M_IF(M_AND(M_PARENTHESIS_P(value), M_TEST_METHOD_P(EMPLACE_TYPE, M_GET_VALUE_OPLIST oplist))) \
4739 (M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2YY, M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2YN)(dst, oplist, key, value)
4740#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2N(dst, oplist, key, value) \
4741 M_IF(M_AND(M_PARENTHESIS_P(value), M_TEST_METHOD_P(EMPLACE_TYPE, M_GET_VALUE_OPLIST oplist))) \
4742 (M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2NY, M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2NN)(dst, oplist, key, value)
4743#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2YY(dst, oplist, key, value) \
4744 M_C(M_GET_NAME oplist, _emplace_key_val) \
4745 (dst, M_INIT_KEY_VAI_ID key, M_INIT_KEY_VAI_ID value)
4746#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2YN(dst, oplist, key, value) \
4747 M_C(M_GET_NAME oplist, _emplace_key)(dst, M_INIT_KEY_VAI_ID key, value)
4748#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2NY(dst, oplist, key, value) \
4749 M_C(M_GET_NAME oplist, _emplace_val)(dst, key, M_INIT_KEY_VAI_ID value)
4750#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI_FUNC_P2NN(dst, oplist, key, value) \
4751 M_CALL_SET_KEY(oplist, dst, key, value)
4752#define M_INIT_KEY_VAI_ID(a) a
4753
4754
4755/* Provide an INIT_WITH method that uses the EMPLACE_TYPE definition
4756 by performing a _Generic selection on the first given argument
4757 for all selections that match the number of arguments given to INIT_WITH,
4758 and uses the provided init_func functions for constructing the variable.
4759 Needs to be defined in the OPLIST with API_1
4760 Only LIST based emplace_type supported as we need a dedicated init_func
4761 FIXME: M_MAP2 allowed in INIT_WITH? (Seems working)
4762*/
4763#define M_INIT_WITH_THROUGH_EMPLACE_TYPE(oplist, dst, ...) \
4764 M_IF(M_TEST_METHOD_P(EMPLACE_TYPE, oplist)) \
4765 (M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_TYPE_2, M_INIT_WITH_NOT_AVAILABLE) \
4766 (oplist, dst, __VA_ARGS__)
4767#define M_INIT_WITH_NOT_AVAILABLE(oplist, dst, ...) \
4768 M_STATIC_ASSERT(false, M_LIB_ILLEGAL_EMPLACE_TYPE, \
4769 "Cannot INIT_WITH through EMPLACE_TYPE, such operator is not provided in the given oplist: " #oplist)
4770#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_TYPE_2(oplist, dst, ...) \
4771 M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_TYPE_3(M_GET_EMPLACE_TYPE oplist, oplist, dst, __VA_ARGS__)
4772#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_TYPE_3(emplace_type, oplist, dst, ...) \
4773 M_IF(M_KEYWORD_P(LIST,emplace_type)) \
4774 (M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_TYPE_4, M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_TYPE_FAIL) \
4775 (emplace_type, oplist, dst, __VA_ARGS__)
4776#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_TYPE_FAIL(emplace_type, oplist, dst, ...) \
4777 M_STATIC_ASSERT(false, M_LIB_ILLEGAL_EMPLACE_TYPE, \
4778 "Only LIST based EMPLACE_TYPE with explicit init_func (No INIT_WITH) are supported")
4779#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_TYPE_4(emplace_type, oplist, dst, ...) \
4780 _Generic( M_RET_ARG1( __VA_ARGS__, ) \
4781 M_MAP2(M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_APPLY, \
4782 (oplist, dst, M_ADD(2, M_NARGS(__VA_ARGS__)), __VA_ARGS__), \
4783 M_KEYWORD_TO_VA_ARGS(LIST, emplace_type)) \
4784 , default: M_STATIC_ASSERT(M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_ASSERT_COND(emplace_type, __VA_ARGS__), M_LIB_ILLEGAL_EMPLACE_TYPE, \
4785 "Cannot find any matching constructor for the type of " \
4786 M_AS_STR (M_RET_ARG1( __VA_ARGS__, ) \
4787 " with " M_AS_STR(M_NARGS(__VA_ARGS__)) " arguments in " M_AS_STR(emplace_type) )) \
4788 )
4789/* arglist is (oplist, dest, NARGS, args...) emplace_type is (suffix, init_func, types...) */
4790#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_APPLY(arglist, emplace_type) \
4791 M_IF(M_EQUAL(M_RET_ARG3 arglist, M_NARGS emplace_type)) \
4792 (M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_APPLY_2, M_EAT)(arglist, emplace_type)
4793#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_APPLY_2(arglist, emplace_type) \
4794 , M_RET_ARG3 emplace_type : M_APPLY_API(M_RET_ARG2 emplace_type, M_RET_ARG1 arglist, M_RET_ARG2 arglist M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR((M_TAIL_3 arglist), emplace_type) )
4795#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR(arglist, emplace_type) \
4796 M_MAP3( M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR_MULTI_FUNC, emplace_type, \
4797 M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR_ID arglist)
4798#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR_MULTI_FUNC(emplace_type, num, arg) \
4799 , M_AS_TYPE(M_RET_ARG(M_ADD(num, 2), M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR_ID emplace_type), arg)
4800#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR_ID(...) __VA_ARGS__ /* M_ID macro */
4801// Workaround to provide a nice static failure at compile time if we cannot find a matching type.
4802#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_ASSERT_COND(emplace_type, ...) \
4803 _Generic( M_RET_ARG1( __VA_ARGS__, ) \
4804 M_MAP2(M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_ASSERT_COND_APPLY, M_ADD(2, M_NARGS(__VA_ARGS__)), \
4805 M_KEYWORD_TO_VA_ARGS(LIST, emplace_type)) \
4806 , default: 0 )
4807#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_ASSERT_COND_APPLY(args, emplace_type) \
4808 M_IF(M_EQUAL(args, M_NARGS emplace_type)) \
4809 (M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_ASSERT_COND_APPLY_2, M_EAT)(args, emplace_type)
4810#define M_INIT_WITH_EMPLACE_LIST_ASSERT_COND_APPLY_2(args, emplace_type) \
4811 , M_RET_ARG3 emplace_type : 1
4812

4815/************************************************************/
4816/******************* EMPLACE GENERATION ********************/
4817/************************************************************/
4818
4819/* Expand to the list of emplace type with their variable name
4820 to use in the function declaration (start with a ,) */
4821#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR(prefix, emplace_type) \
4822 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P( emplace_type ))(M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_MULTI, M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_SINGLE)(prefix, emplace_type)
4823#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_MULTI(prefix, emplace_type) \
4824 M_MAP3(M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_MULTI_F, prefix, M_ID emplace_type)
4825#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_MULTI_F(prefix, num, type) \
4826 , type const M_C(prefix, num)
4827#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_SINGLE(prefix, emplace_type) \
4828 , emplace_type const prefix
4829
4830/* Expand to the list of emplace type with their variable name
4831 to use in the function declaration (doesn't start with a , but slower) */
4832#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_ALTER(prefix, emplace_type) \
4833 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P( emplace_type ))(M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_ALTER_MULTI, M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_ALTER_SINGLE)(prefix, emplace_type)
4834#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_ALTER_MULTI(prefix, emplace_type) \
4835 M_MAP3(M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_ALTER_MULTI_F, prefix, M_ID emplace_type)
4836#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_ALTER_MULTI_F(prefix, num, type) \
4837 M_IF(M_EQUAL(1, num))( /*void*/, M_DEFERRED_COMMA) type const M_C(prefix, num)
4838#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR_ALTER_SINGLE(prefix, emplace_type) \
4839 emplace_type const prefix
4840
4841/* Expand to the list of variable name based on the the declaration with
4842 emplace type to use in the INIT_WITH or specific method call (start with a ,) */
4843#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR(prefix, emplace_type) \
4844 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P( emplace_type ))(M_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR_MULTI, M_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR_SINGLE)(prefix, emplace_type)
4845#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR_MULTI(prefix, emplace_type) \
4846 , M_MAP2_C( M_C, prefix, M_SEQ(1, M_NARGS emplace_type) )
4847#define M_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR_SINGLE(prefix, emplace_type) \
4848 , prefix
4849
4850
4851/* Call either INIT_WITH with the prefixed arguments used for emplace
4852 if init_func is the keyword INIT_WITH
4853 or with the user provided init_func (otherwise) */
4854#define M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC(prefix, init_func, oplist, dest, emplace_type) \
4855 M_IF(M_KEYWORD_P(INIT_WITH, init_func)) \
4856 (M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC_INIT_WITH, M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC_USER_PROVIDED) \
4857 (prefix, init_func, oplist, dest, emplace_type)
4858#define M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC_INIT_WITH(prefix, init_func, oplist, dest, emplace_type) \
4859 /* If INIT_FUNC==INIT_WITH, classic use of INIT_WITH operator */ \
4860 M_CALL_INIT_WITH(oplist, dest M_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR(prefix, emplace_type) )
4861#define M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC_USER_PROVIDED(prefix, init_func, oplist, dest, emplace_type) \
4862 /* Use the user provided init_func instead (with API transformation) */ \
4863 M_APPLY_API(init_func, oplist, dest M_EMPLACE_LIST_VAR(prefix, emplace_type) )
4864
4865
4866/* Generate one or several definitions for the EMPLACE methods
4867 using the operator EMPLACE_TYPE to get the suitable user types
4868 and the user provided macro to expand the function definition.
4869 The user provided a macro which prototype is
4870 macro(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, init_func, exp_emplace_type)
4871 It is suitable for container with a single type of data within.
4872 NOTE: Use internally, M_MAP2, M_MAP2_C & M_MAP3
4873 */
4874#define M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro) \
4875 M_ID( \
4876 M_IF(M_TEST_METHOD_ALTER_P(EMPLACE_TYPE, oplist)) \
4877 (M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_EXPAND, M_EAT) \
4878 (name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro, M_GET_EMPLACE_TYPE oplist) \
4879 )
4880/* One EMPLACE_TYPE operator is defined ==> Perform the emplace function expansion.
4881 If the emplace type starts with parenthesis, it is only one with multiple args */
4882#define M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_EXPAND(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro, emplace_type) \
4883 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P(emplace_type)) \
4884 (M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_SINGLE_EXPAND, M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_EXPAND_P2) \
4885 (name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro, emplace_type)
4886/* Test if it starts with LIST, in which case, multiple emplace methods have to be defined */
4887#define M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_EXPAND_P2(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro, emplace_type) \
4888 M_IF(M_KEYWORD_P(LIST, emplace_type)) \
4889 (M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_LIST_EXPAND, M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_SINGLE_EXPAND) \
4890 (name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro, emplace_type)
4891/* Define & expand multiple emplace methods */
4892#define M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_LIST_EXPAND(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro, emplace_type) \
4893 M_MAP2(M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_SUFFIX, (name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro), M_KEYWORD_TO_VA_ARGS(LIST, emplace_type))
4894/* Let the arguments be expanded before calling the definition macro */
4895#define M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_SUFFIX(trio, list) M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_SUFFIX2(M_ID trio, M_ID list)
4896/* Let the arguments be expanded before calling the definition macro */
4897#define M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_SUFFIX2(...) M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_SUFFIX3(__VA_ARGS__)
4898/* Everything is now proprely expanded. Just call the original macro (with a properly expanded emplace type) */
4899#define M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_SUFFIX3(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro, sup_suffix, init_func, ...) \
4900 macro(name, name_t, M_C_EMPTY(function_name, sup_suffix), oplist, init_func, (__VA_ARGS__) )
4901/* Define & expand one emplace method by using the definition macro */
4902#define M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_DEF_SINGLE_EXPAND(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, macro, emplace_type) \
4903 macro(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, INIT_WITH, emplace_type)
4904
4905
4906/* Generate one or several definitions for the EMPLACE methods
4907 using the operator EMPLACE_TYPE to get the suitable user types
4908 and the user provided macro to expand the function definition.
4909 The user provided three macros which prototype are
4910 macro(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, key_init_func, val_init_func, key_emplace_type, val_emplace_type)
4911 first macro is for generating emplacing with both key & value are emplaced,
4912 second macro is for generating emplacing with only key is emplaced,
4913 third macro is for generating emplacing with only value is emplaced,
4914 It is suitable for associative array containers.
4915 NOTE: Use internally, M_MAP2, M_MAP2_C & M_MAP3
4916 */
4917#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val) \
4918 M_IF(M_TEST_METHOD_ALTER_P(EMPLACE_TYPE, key_oplist)) \
4919 (M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_KEY_OR_BOTH, M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_VALUE_OR_NONE) \
4920 (name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val)
4921/* We have a key EMPLACE_TYPE. We can generate key only or both emplace functions */
4922#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_KEY_OR_BOTH(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val) \
4923 M_IF(M_TEST_METHOD_ALTER_P(EMPLACE_TYPE, val_oplist)) \
4924 (M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_BOTH, M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_KEY) \
4925 (name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, M_GET_EMPLACE_TYPE key_oplist, M_GET_EMPLACE_TYPE val_oplist)
4926/* We have a value EMPLACE_TYPE. We can generate value only or no emplace functions */
4927#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_VALUE_OR_NONE(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val) \
4928 M_IF(M_TEST_METHOD_ALTER_P(EMPLACE_TYPE, val_oplist)) \
4929 (M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_VAL, M_EAT) \
4930 (name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_val, macro_key, macro_val, M_GET_EMPLACE_TYPE key_oplist, M_GET_EMPLACE_TYPE val_oplist)
4931
4932/* Generate KEY only emplace functions */
4933/* One EMPLACE_TYPE operator is defined ==> Perform the emplace function expansion.
4934 If the emplace type starts with parenthesis, it is only one with multiple args */
4935#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_KEY(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type) \
4936 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P(key_emp_type)) \
4937 (M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SINGLE_EXPAND_KEY, M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_P2_KEY) \
4938 (name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type)
4939/* Test if it starts with LIST, in which case, multiple emplace methods have to be defined */
4940#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_P2_KEY(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type) \
4941 M_IF(M_KEYWORD_P(LIST, key_emp_type)) \
4942 (M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_LIST_EXPAND_KEY, M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SINGLE_EXPAND_KEY) \
4943 (name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type)
4944/* Define & expand multiple emplace methods with the _key prefix */
4945#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_LIST_EXPAND_KEY(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type) \
4946 M_MAP2(M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX_KEY, (name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_key, key_emp_type, val_emp_type), M_KEYWORD_TO_VA_ARGS(LIST, key_emp_type))
4947/* Let the arguments be expanded before calling the definition macro */
4948#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX_KEY(trio, list) M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX2_KEY(M_ID trio, M_ID list)
4949/* Let the arguments be expanded before calling the definition macro */
4950#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX2_KEY(...) M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX3_KEY(__VA_ARGS__)
4951/* Everything is now proprely expanded. Just call the original macro (with a properly expanded emplace type) */
4952#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX3_KEY(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro, key_emp_type, val_emp_type, sup_suffix, init_func, ...) \
4953 macro(name, name_t, M_C3_EMPTY(function_name, _key, sup_suffix), key_oplist, val_oplist, init_func, val_init_func, (__VA_ARGS__), val_list )
4954/* Define & expand one emplace method by using the definition macro */
4955#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SINGLE_EXPAND_KEY(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type) \
4956 macro_key(name, name_t, M_C(function_name, _key), key_oplist, val_oplist, INIT_WITH, none, key_emp_type, val_emp_type)
4957
4958/* Generate VALUE only emplace functions */
4959/* One EMPLACE_TYPE operator is defined ==> Perform the emplace function expansion.
4960 If the emplace type starts with parenthesis, it is only one with multiple args */
4961#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_VAL(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type) \
4962 M_IF(M_PARENTHESIS_P(val_emp_type)) \
4963 (M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SINGLE_EXPAND_VAL, M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_P2_VAL) \
4964 (name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type)
4965/* Test if it starts with LIST, in which case, multiple emplace methods have to be defined */
4966#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_EXPAND_P2_VAL(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type) \
4967 M_IF(M_KEYWORD_P(LIST, val_emp_type)) \
4968 (M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_LIST_EXPAND_VAL, M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SINGLE_EXPAND_VAL) \
4969 (name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type)
4970/* Define & expand multiple emplace methods with the _val prefix */
4971#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_LIST_EXPAND_VAL(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_both, macro_key, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type) \
4972 M_MAP2(M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX_VAL, (name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro_val, key_emp_type, val_emp_type), M_KEYWORD_TO_VA_ARGS(LIST, val_emp_type))
4973/* Let the arguments be expanded before calling the definition macro */
4974#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX_VAL(trio, list) M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX2_VAL(M_ID trio, M_ID list)
4975/* Let the arguments be expanded before calling the definition macro */
4976#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX2_VAL(...) M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX3_VAL(__VA_ARGS__)
4977/* Everything is now proprely expanded. Just call the original macro (with a properly expanded emplace type) */
4978#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRAY_DEF_SUFFIX3_VAL(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, macro, key_emp_type, val_emp_type, sup_suffix, init_func, ...) \
4979 macro(name, name_t, M_C3_EMPTY(function_name, _val, sup_suffix), key_oplist, val_oplist, key_init_func, init_func, val_list, (__VA_ARGS__) )
4980/* Define & expand one emplace method by using the definition macro */

5020/* Definition of the emplace_back function for associative arrays.
5021 It is defined here so that this definition is shared accross different
5022 kind of associative array (RB-Tree, Hashmap, OA-Hashmap, B+Tree, ...)
5023 This definition is far from being efficient but works for the current interface.
5024 3 macros are needed: one when we emplace both key & value, one for key only
5025 one for value only.
5026*/
5027#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRA1_BOTH_GENE(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, key_init_func, val_init_func, key_emplace_type, val_emplace_type) \
5028 M_INLINE void \
5029 function_name(name_t v \
5030 M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR(akey, key_emplace_type) \
5031 M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR(aval, val_emplace_type) \
5032 ){ \
5033 M_F(name, _key_ct) key; \
5034 M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC(akey, key_init_func, key_oplist, key, key_emplace_type); \
5035 M_F(name, _value_ct) *val; \
5036 val = M_F(name, _safe_get)(v, key); \
5037 M_CALL_CLEAR(val_oplist, *val); \
5038 M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC(aval, val_init_func, val_oplist, *val, val_emplace_type); \
5039 M_CALL_CLEAR(key_oplist, key); \
5040 } \
5041
5042#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRA1_KEY_GENE(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, key_init_func, val_init_func, key_emplace_type, val_emplace_type) \
5043 M_INLINE void \
5044 function_name(name_t v \
5045 M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR(akey, key_emplace_type) \
5046 , M_F(name, _value_ct) const val \
5047 ){ \
5048 M_F(name, _key_ct) key; \
5049 M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC(akey, key_init_func, key_oplist, key, key_emplace_type); \
5050 M_F(name, _set_at)(v, key, val); \
5051 M_CALL_CLEAR(key_oplist, key); \
5052 } \
5053
5054#define M_EMPLACE_ASS_ARRA1_VAL_GENE(name, name_t, function_name, key_oplist, val_oplist, key_init_func, val_init_func, key_emplace_type, val_emplace_type) \
5055 M_INLINE void \
5056 function_name(name_t v, M_F(name, _key_ct) const key \
5057 M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR(aval, val_emplace_type) \
5058 ){ \
5059 M_F(name, _value_ct) *val; \
5060 val = M_F(name, _safe_get)(v, key); \
5061 M_CALL_CLEAR(val_oplist, *val); \
5062 M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC(aval, val_init_func, val_oplist, *val, val_emplace_type); \
5063 } \
5064
5065/* Definition of the emplace_back function for queue.
5066 It is defined here so that this definition is shared accross different
5067 kind of kind of queue.
5068 This definition is far from being efficient but works for the current interface.
5069*/
5070#define M_EMPLACE_QUEUE_GENE(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, init_func, exp_emplace_type) \
5071 M_INLINE void \
5072 function_name(name_t v \
5073 M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR(a, exp_emplace_type) ) \
5074 { \
5075 M_GET_TYPE oplist data; \
5076 M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC(a, init_func, oplist, data, exp_emplace_type); \
5077 M_F(name, _push)(v, data); \
5078 M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, data); \
5079 }
5080
5081/* Definition of the get_emplace function for set / map.
5082 It is defined here so that this definition is shared accross different
5083 kind of kind of queue.
5084 This definition is far from being efficient but works for the current interface.
5085*/
5086#define M_EMPLACE_GET_GENE(name, name_t, function_name, oplist, init_func, exp_emplace_type) \
5087 M_INLINE M_F(name, _value_ct) * \
5088 function_name(name_t const v \
5089 M_EMPLACE_LIST_TYPE_VAR(a, exp_emplace_type) ) \
5090 { \
5091 M_GET_TYPE oplist data; \
5092 M_EMPLACE_CALL_FUNC(a, init_func, oplist, data, exp_emplace_type); \
5093 M_F(name, _value_ct) *ret = M_F(name, _get)(v, data); \
5094 M_CALL_CLEAR(oplist, data); \
5095 return ret; \
5096 }

5099/************************************************************/
5100/******************* Exponential Backoff ********************/
5101/************************************************************/
5102
5103/* Can be increased / decreased by user code if needed
5104 to increase / decrease backoff of code */
5105#ifndef M_USE_BACKOFF_MAX_COUNT
5106#define M_USE_BACKOFF_MAX_COUNT 8
5107#endif
5108
5109/* Exponential backoff object.
5110 * An exponential backoff object will increase its wait time
5111 * each time it is called with a pseudo random wait.
5112 * It is used to avoid too many threads trying to grab some atomic
5113 * variables at the same times (it makes the threads waits randomly).
5114 */
5115typedef struct m_core_backoff_s {
5116 unsigned int count; // Number of times it has been run
5117 unsigned int seed; // Initial seed
5118} m_core_backoff_ct[1];
5119
5120/* Initialize a backoff object. */
5121M_INLINE void
5122m_core_backoff_init(m_core_backoff_ct backoff)
5123{
5124 backoff->count = 0;
5125 backoff->seed = 0;
5126}
5127
5128/* Reset the count of the backoff object */
5129M_INLINE void
5130m_core_backoff_reset(m_core_backoff_ct backoff)
5131{
5132 backoff->count = 0;
5133}
5134
5135/* Wait a few nanoseconds using an active loop,
5136 * generating a random number of nanosecond to wait,
5137 * and increment the number of times wait has been called */
5138M_INLINE void
5139m_core_backoff_wait(m_core_backoff_ct backoff)
5140{
5141 if (backoff->count <= 2) {
5142 backoff->count++;
5143 if (backoff->count < 3)
5144 return;
5145 // Use the C function rand to initialize its internal seed.
5146 // It should be good enough for the purpose of the backoff.
5147 // We only do it once if we already have performed several loops
5148 // to avoid paying the cost of 'rand' for the small start.
5149 backoff->seed = (unsigned int) rand();
5150 }
5151 /* x is qualified as volatile to avoid being optimized away
5152 by the compiler in the active sleep loop */
5153 volatile int x = 0;
5154 /* Cheap but fast pseudo random. */
5155 backoff->seed = backoff->seed * 34721 + 17449;
5156 const unsigned int mask = (1U << backoff->count) -1;
5157 const unsigned int count = mask & (backoff->seed >> 8);
5158 /* Active sleep for 'count' times */
5159 for(unsigned int i = 0; i <= count; i++)
5160 x = 0;
5161 (void) x;
5162 /* Increment count for next step if needed */
5163 backoff->count += (backoff->count < M_USE_BACKOFF_MAX_COUNT);
5164}
5165
5166/* Clear the backoff object */
5167M_INLINE void
5168m_core_backoff_clear(m_core_backoff_ct backoff)
5169{
5170 // Nothing to do
5171 (void) backoff;
5172}
5173
5174
5175
5176/************************************************************/
5177/********************** Serialization ***********************/
5178/************************************************************/
5179
5180/* Forward declaration of m_string_t defined in m-string.h */
5181struct m_string_s;
5182
5183/* Serialization Return code:
5184 * - OK & done (object is fully parsed),
5185 * - OK & continue parsing (object is partially parsed)
5186 * - Fail parsing
5187 * - Fail parsing with given arguments (give explicit size)
5188 */
5189typedef enum m_serial_return_code_e {
5190 M_SERIAL_OK_DONE = 0, M_SERIAL_OK_CONTINUE = 1, M_SERIAL_FAIL = 2, M_SERIAL_FAIL_RETRY = 4
5191} m_serial_return_code_t;
5192
5193#if defined(__cplusplus)
5194// C++ doesn't allow mixing enum and integer, so we provided overloaded operators.
5195inline void operator|(m_serial_return_code_t &a, m_serial_return_code_t b)
5196{
5197 a = static_cast<m_serial_return_code_t>(static_cast<int>(a) | static_cast<int>(b));
5198}
5199inline m_serial_return_code_t operator|=(m_serial_return_code_t a, m_serial_return_code_t b)
5200{
5201 return static_cast<m_serial_return_code_t>(static_cast<int>(a) | static_cast<int>(b));
5202}
5203inline m_serial_return_code_t operator&(m_serial_return_code_t a, m_serial_return_code_t b)
5204{
5205 return static_cast<m_serial_return_code_t>(static_cast<int>(a) & static_cast<int>(b));
5206}
5207#endif
5208
5209/* Maximum data size of a serializator structure
5210 * Can be overloaded by user */
5211#ifndef M_USE_SERIAL_MAX_DATA_SIZE
5212#define M_USE_SERIAL_MAX_DATA_SIZE 4
5213#endif
5214
5215/* Different types of types that can be stored in a serial object to represent it:
5216 * a boolean
5217 * different kind of integers
5218 * different kind of floats
5219 * a size
5220 * a pointer to something.
5221 * a serial return code
5222 */
5223typedef union m_serial_ll_u {
5224 bool b;
5225 char c;
5226 int i;
5227 long l;
5228 long long ll;
5229 float f;
5230 double d;
5231 long double e;
5232 size_t s;
5233 uintptr_t u;
5234 void *p;
5235 const char *cstr;
5236 m_serial_return_code_t r;
5237} m_serial_ll_ct;
5238
5239/* Object to handle the construction of a serial write/read of an object
5240 that needs multiple calls (array, map, ...)
5241 It is common to all calls to the same object.
5242 It shall be used as a local state of the object being parsed */
5243typedef struct m_serial_local_s {
5244 m_serial_ll_ct data[M_USE_SERIAL_MAX_DATA_SIZE];
5245} m_serial_local_t[1];
5246
5247/* Object to handle the generic serial read of an object:
5248 * - m_interface is the pointer to the constant interface object that has all callbacks
5249 * - tmp is temporary variable used localy by the non recursive serializer (not to be used by serializer)
5250 * - data is user defined data to use by the serialization object as it wants
5251 * NOTE: 'interface' word cannot be used as a field name as some system headers
5252 * define it as a macro.
5253 * */
5254typedef struct m_serial_read_s {
5255 const struct m_serial_read_interface_s *m_interface;
5256 m_serial_ll_ct tmp;
5257 m_serial_ll_ct data[M_USE_SERIAL_MAX_DATA_SIZE];
5258} m_serial_read_t[1];
5259
5260/* Interface that has to be exported by the serial read object.
5261 * All function pointers shall be not null.
5262 */
5263typedef struct m_serial_read_interface_s {
5264 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_boolean)(m_serial_read_t,bool *);
5265 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_integer)(m_serial_read_t, long long *, const size_t size_of_type);
5266 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_float)(m_serial_read_t, long double *, const size_t size_of_type);
5267 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_string)(m_serial_read_t, struct m_string_s *);
5268 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_array_start)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_read_t, size_t *);
5269 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_array_next)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_read_t);
5270 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_map_start)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_read_t, size_t *);
5271 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_map_value)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_read_t);
5272 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_map_next)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_read_t);
5273 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_tuple_start)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_read_t);
5274 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_tuple_id)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_read_t, const char *const field_name [], const int max, int *);
5275 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_variant_start)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_read_t, const char *const field_name[], const int max, int*);
5276 m_serial_return_code_t (*read_variant_end)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_read_t);
5277} m_serial_read_interface_t;
5278
5279
5280/* Object to handle the generic serial write of an object:
5281 * - m_interface is the pointer to the constant interface object that has all callbacks
5282 * - tmp is temporary variable used localy by the non recursive serializer
5283 * - data is user defined data to use by the serialization object as it wants
5284 * NOTE: 'interface' word cannot be used as a field name as some system headers
5285 * define it as a macro.
5286 * */
5287typedef struct m_serial_write_s {
5288 const struct m_serial_write_interface_s *m_interface;
5289 m_serial_ll_ct tmp;
5290 m_serial_ll_ct data[M_USE_SERIAL_MAX_DATA_SIZE];
5291} m_serial_write_t[1];
5292
5293/* Interface that has to be exported by the serial write object.
5294 * All function pointers shall be not null.
5295 */
5296typedef struct m_serial_write_interface_s {
5297 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_boolean)(m_serial_write_t,const bool data);
5298 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_integer)(m_serial_write_t,const long long data, const size_t size_of_type);
5299 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_float)(m_serial_write_t, const long double data, const size_t size_of_type);
5300 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_string)(m_serial_write_t,const char data[], size_t len);
5301 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_array_start)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t, const size_t number_of_elements);
5302 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_array_next)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t);
5303 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_array_end)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t);
5304 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_map_start)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t, const size_t number_of_elements);
5305 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_map_value)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t);
5306 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_map_next)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t);
5307 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_map_end)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t);
5308 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_tuple_start)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t);
5309 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_tuple_id)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t, const char * const field_name[], const int max, const int index);
5310 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_tuple_end)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t);
5311 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_variant_start)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t, const char * const field_name[], const int max, const int index);
5312 m_serial_return_code_t (*write_variant_end)(m_serial_local_t, m_serial_write_t);
5313} m_serial_write_interface_t;

5320#define M_OUT_SERIAL_DEFAULT_ARG(serial, x) \

5323 char: (serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, M_AS_TYPE(char,(x)), sizeof (x)), \
5324 signed char: (serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, M_AS_TYPE(signed char,(x)), sizeof (x)), \
5325 unsigned char: (serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, (long long) M_AS_TYPE(unsigned char,(x)), sizeof (x)), \
5326 signed short: (serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, M_AS_TYPE(signed short,(x)), sizeof (x)), \
5327 unsigned short: (serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, (long long) M_AS_TYPE(unsigned short,(x)), sizeof (x)), \
5328 signed int: (serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, M_AS_TYPE(signed int,(x)), sizeof (x)), \
5329 unsigned int: (serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, (long long) M_AS_TYPE(unsigned int,(x)), sizeof (x)), \
5330 long int: (serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, M_AS_TYPE(long,(x)), sizeof (x)), \
5331 unsigned long int: (serial)->m_interface->write_integer(serial, (long long) M_AS_TYPE(unsigned long,(x)), sizeof (x)), \

5342/* Convert a Serialized data to a C default variale (bool, integer, float)
5343 * by calling the serializer interface associated to the type of the object.
5344 * NOTE: Supports only C11.
5345*/
5346#define M_IN_SERIAL_DEFAULT_ARG(xptr, serial) \
5347 _Generic(((void)0,*(xptr)), \
5348 bool: (serial)->m_interface->read_boolean(serial, M_AS_TYPE(bool *, xptr)), \
5349 char: m_core_in_serial_char(serial, M_AS_TYPE(char*,xptr)), \
5350 signed char: m_core_in_serial_schar(serial, M_AS_TYPE(signed char*,xptr)), \
5351 unsigned char: m_core_in_serial_uchar(serial, M_AS_TYPE(unsigned char*,xptr)), \
5352 signed short: m_core_in_serial_sshort(serial, M_AS_TYPE(signed short*,xptr)), \
5353 unsigned short: m_core_in_serial_ushort(serial, M_AS_TYPE(unsigned short*,xptr)), \
5354 signed int: m_core_in_serial_sint(serial, M_AS_TYPE(signed int*,xptr)), \
5355 unsigned int: m_core_in_serial_uint(serial, M_AS_TYPE(unsigned int*,xptr)), \
5356 long int: m_core_in_serial_slong(serial, M_AS_TYPE(long*,xptr)), \

5368/* Helper functions for M_IN_SERIAL_DEFAULT_ARG
5369 as we need to define a function per supported type in the generic expression */
5370#define M_IN_SERIAL_DEFAULT_TYPE_DEF(name, type, func, promoted_type) \
5371 M_INLINE m_serial_return_code_t \
5372 name (m_serial_read_t serial, type *ptr) \
5373 { \
5374 promoted_type i; \
5375 m_serial_return_code_t r; \
5376 r = serial->m_interface->func(serial, &i, sizeof (type)); \
5377 *ptr = (type) i; \
5378 return r; \
5379 }

5396/* Helper function for M_ENUM_IN_SERIAL */
5397M_INLINE long long
5398m_core_in_serial_enum(m_serial_read_t serial)
5399{
5400 long long i;
5401 /* Store the return code temporary in the serialize object */
5402 serial->tmp.r = serial->m_interface->read_integer(serial, &i, sizeof (long long));
5403 return i;
5404}

5406/* Encapsulation of strlen to avoid warnings in M_OUT_SERIAL_DEFAULT_ARG
5407 * because of expanded code will call strlen with NULL (which is illegal)
5408 * However, the branch where it is called is unreachable, so the warning
5409 * is not justified. */
5410M_INLINE size_t
5411m_core_out_serial_strlen(const char s[])
5412{
5413 M_ASSERT(s != NULL);
5414 return strlen(s);
5415}
5416
5417/* Encapsulation of returning error,
5418 * A serializer should return 'm_core_serial_fail()' instead of directly
5419 * M_SERIAL_FAIL
5420 * so that a breakpoint can be put on this function for debugging purpose.
5421 */
5422M_INLINE m_serial_return_code_t
5423m_core_serial_fail(void)
5424{
5425 return M_SERIAL_FAIL;
5426}
